SIMPLE: strait-laced
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strait-laced
<hw>Strait"-laced`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Bound with stays.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let nature have scope to fashion the body as she thinks best; we
have few well-shaped that are <qex>strait-laced</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Restricted; stiff; constrained.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Rigid in opinion; strict in manners or
morals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straitly</ent>⟦br⟧
